01Gn 19:37 When the older daughter gave birth to a son, she named him Moab��. He became the ancestor of the nation now known as the Moabites. / ��Moab sounds like a Hebrew term that means "from father"
01Gn 19:38 When the younger daughter gave birth to a son, she named him Ben-ammi��. He became the ancestor of the nation now known as the Ammonites. / ��Ben-ammi means "son of my kinsman"
01Gn 20:1 Abraham moved south to the Negev and lived for a while between Kadesh and Shur, and then he moved on to Gerar. While living there as a foreigner,
01Gn 20:2 Abraham introduced his wife, Sarah, by saying, "She is my sister." So King Abimelech of Gerar sent for Sarah and had her brought to him at his palace.
01Gn 20:3 But that night God came to Abimelech in a dream and told him, "You are a dead man, for that woman you have taken is already married!"
01Gn 20:4 But Abimelech had not slept with her yet, so he said, "Lord, will you destroy an innocent nation?
01Gn 20:5 Didn't Abraham tell me, 'She is my sister'? And she herself said, 'Yes, he is my brother.' I acted in complete innocence! My hands are clean."
01Gn 20:6 In the dream God responded, "Yes, I know you are innocent. That's why I kept you from sinning against me, and why I did not let you touch her.
01Gn 20:7 Now return the woman to her husband, and he will pray for you, for he is a prophet. Then you will live. But if you don't return her to him, you can be sure that you and all your people will die."
01Gn 20:8 Abimelech got up early the next morning and quickly called all his servants together. When he told them what had happened, his men were terrified.
01Gn 20:9 Then Abimelech called for Abraham. "What have you done to us?" he demanded. "What crime have I committed that deserves treatment like this, making me and my kingdom guilty of this great sin? No one should ever do what you have done!
01Gn 20:10 Whatever possessed you to do such a thing?"
01Gn 20:11 Abraham replied, "I thought, 'This is a godless place. They will want my wife and will kill me to get her.'
01Gn 20:12 And she really is my sister, for we both have the same father, but different mothers. And I married her.
