01Gn 20:14 Then Abimelech took some of his sheep and goats, cattle, and male and female servants, and he presented them to Abraham. He also returned his wife, Sarah, to him.
01Gn 20:15 Then Abimelech said, "Look over my land and choose any place where you would like to live."
01Gn 20:16 And he said to Sarah, "Look, I am giving your 'brother' 1,000 pieces of silver�� in the presence of all these witnesses. This is to compensate you for any wrong I may have done to you. This will settle any claim against me, and your reputation is cleared." / ��Hebrew 1,000 [shekels] of silver, about 25 pounds or 11.4 kilograms in weight
01Gn 20:17 Then Abraham prayed to God, and God healed Abimelech, his wife, and his female servants, so they could have children.
