01Gn 22:1 Some time later, God tested Abraham's faith. "Abraham!" God called. "Yes," he replied. "Here I am."
01Gn 22:2 "Take your son, your only son - yes, Isaac, whom you love so much - and go to the land of Moriah. Go and sacrifice him as a burnt offering on one of the mountains, which I will show you."
01Gn 22:3 The next morning Abraham got up early. He saddled his donkey and took two of his servants with him, along with his son, Isaac. Then he chopped wood for a fire for a burnt offering and set out for the place God had told him about.
01Gn 22:4 On the third day of their journey, Abraham looked up and saw the place in the distance.
01Gn 22:5 "Stay here with the donkey," Abraham told the servants. "The boy and I will travel a little farther. We will worship there, and then we will come right back."
01Gn 22:6 So Abraham placed the wood for the burnt offering on Isaac's shoulders, while he himself carried the fire and the knife. As the two of them walked on together,
01Gn 22:7 Isaac turned to Abraham and said, "Father?" "Yes, my son?" Abraham replied. "We have the fire and the wood," the boy said, "but where is the sheep for the burnt offering?"
01Gn 22:8 "God will provide a sheep for the burnt offering, my son," Abraham answered. And they both walked on together.
01Gn 22:9 When they arrived at the place where God had told him to go, Abraham built an altar and arranged the wood on it. Then he tied his son, Isaac, and laid him on the altar on top of the wood.
01Gn 22:10 And Abraham picked up the knife to kill his son as a sacrifice.
01Gn 22:11 At that moment the angel of the LORD called to him from heaven, "Abraham! Abraham!" "Yes," Abraham replied. "Here I am!"
01Gn 22:12 "Don't lay a hand on the boy!" the angel said. "Do not hurt him in any way, for now I know that you truly fear God. You have not withheld from me even your son, your only son."
01Gn 22:13 Then Abraham looked up and saw a ram caught by its horns in a thicket. So he took the ram and sacrificed it as a burnt offering in place of his son.
01Gn 22:14 Abraham named the place Yahweh-Yireh (which means "the LORD will provide"). To this day, people still use that name as a proverb�� "On the mountain of the LORD it will be provided."
01Gn 22:15 Then the angel of the LORD called again to Abraham from heaven.
01Gn 22:16 "This is what the LORD says�� Because you have obeyed me and have not withheld even your son, your only son, I swear by my own name that
01Gn 22:17 I will certainly bless you. I will multiply your descendants�� beyond number, like the stars in the sky and the sand on the seashore. Your descendants will conquer the cities of their enemies. / ��Hebrew seed; also in 22.17b, 18
01Gn 22:18 And through your descendants all the nations of the earth will be blessed - all because you have obeyed me."
01Gn 22:19 Then they returned to the servants and traveled back to Beersheba, where Abraham continued to live.
01Gn 22:20 Soon after this, Abraham heard that Milcah, his brother Nahor's wife, had borne Nahor eight sons.
