01Gn 23:14 Ephron answered Abraham,
01Gn 23:15 "My lord, please listen to me. The land is worth 400 pieces�� of silver, but what is that between friends? Go ahead and bury your dead." / ��Hebrew 400 shekels, about 10 pounds or 4.6 kilograms in weight; also in 23.16
01Gn 23:16 So Abraham agreed to Ephron's price and paid the amount he had suggested - 400 pieces of silver, weighed according to the market standard. The Hittite elders witnessed the transaction.
