03Lv 6:29 Any male from a priest's family may eat from this offering; it is most holy.
03Lv 6:30 But the offering for sin may not be eaten if its blood was brought into the Tabernacle as an offering for purification�� in the Holy Place. It must be completely burned with fire. / ��Or an offering to make atonement
03Lv 7:1 "These are the instructions for the guilt offering. It is most holy.
03Lv 7:2 The animal sacrificed as a guilt offering must be slaughtered at the place where the burnt offerings are slaughtered, and its blood must be splattered against all sides of the altar.
03Lv 7:3 The priest will then offer all its fat on the altar, including the fat of the broad tail, the fat around the internal organs,
