03Lv 13:47 "Now suppose mildew�� contaminates some woolen or linen clothing, / ��Traditionally rendered leprosy. The Hebrew term used throughout this passage is the same term used for the various skin diseases described in 13.1-46
03Lv 13:48 woolen or linen fabric, the hide of an animal, or anything made of leather.
