04Nm 27:1 One day a petition was presented by the daughters of Zelophehad - Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah. Their father, Zelophehad, was a descendant of Hepher son of Gilead, son of Makir, son of Manasseh, son of Joseph.
04Nm 27:2 These women stood before Moses, Eleazar the priest, the tribal leaders, and the entire community at the entrance of the Tabernacle��. / ��Hebrew the Tent of Meeting
04Nm 27:3 "Our father died in the wilderness," they said. "He was not among Korah's followers, who rebelled against the LORD; he died because of his own sin. But he had no sons.
04Nm 27:4 Why should the name of our father disappear from his clan just because he had no sons? Give us property along with the rest of our relatives."
04Nm 27:5 So Moses brought their case before the LORD.
04Nm 27:6 And the LORD replied to Moses,
04Nm 27:7 "The claim of the daughters of Zelophehad is legitimate. You must give them a grant of land along with their father's relatives. Assign them the property that would have been given to their father.
04Nm 27:8 "And give the following instructions to the people of Israel�� If a man dies and has no son, then give his inheritance to his daughters.
04Nm 27:9 And if he has no daughter either, transfer his inheritance to his brothers.
04Nm 27:10 If he has no brothers, give his inheritance to his father's brothers.
04Nm 27:11 But if his father has no brothers, give his inheritance to the nearest relative in his clan. This is a legal requirement for the people of Israel, just as the LORD commanded Moses."
04Nm 27:12 One day the LORD said to Moses, "Climb one of the mountains east of the river��, and look out over the land I have given the people of Israel. / ��Or the mountains of Abarim
04Nm 27:13 After you have seen it, you will die like your brother, Aaron,
04Nm 27:14 for you both rebelled against my instructions in the wilderness of Zin. When the people of Israel rebelled, you failed to demonstrate my holiness to them at the waters." (These are the waters of Meribah at Kadesh�� in the wilderness of Zin.) / ��Hebrew waters of Meribath-kadesh
04Nm 27:15 Then Moses said to the LORD,
04Nm 27:16 "O LORD, you are the God who gives breath to all creatures. Please appoint a new man as leader for the community.
04Nm 27:17 Give them someone who will guide them wherever they go and will lead them into battle, so the community of the LORD will not be like sheep without a shepherd."
04Nm 27:18 The LORD replied, "Take Joshua son of Nun, who has the Spirit in him, and lay your hands on him.
04Nm 27:19 Present him to Eleazar the priest before the whole community, and publicly commission him to lead the people.
04Nm 27:20 Transfer some of your authority to him so the whole community of Israel will obey him.
04Nm 27:21 When direction from the LORD is needed, Joshua will stand before Eleazar the priest, who will use the Urim - one of the sacred lots cast before the LORD - to determine his will. This is how Joshua and the rest of the community of Israel will determine everything they should do."
04Nm 27:22 So Moses did as the LORD commanded. He presented Joshua to Eleazar the priest and the whole community.
04Nm 27:23 Moses laid his hands on him and commissioned him to lead the people, just as the LORD had commanded through Moses.
04Nm 28:1 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 28:2 "Give these instructions to the people of Israel�� The offerings you present as special gifts are a pleasing aroma to me; they are my food. See to it that they are brought at the appointed times and offered according to my instructions.
