04Nm 28:11 "On the first day of each month, present an extra burnt offering to the LORD of two young bulls, one ram, and seven one-year-old male lambs, all with no defects.
04Nm 28:12 These must be accompanied by grain offerings of choice flour moistened with olive oil - six quarts�� with each bull, four quarts with the ram, / ��Hebrew 3/10 of an ephah [6.6 liters]; also in 28.20, 28
04Nm 28:13 and two quarts with each lamb. This burnt offering will be a special gift, a pleasing aroma to the LORD.
04Nm 28:14 You must also present a liquid offering with each sacrifice�� two quarts�� of wine for each bull, a third of a gallon�� for the ram, and one quart�� for each lamb. Present this monthly burnt offering on the first day of each month throughout the year. / ��Hebrew 1/2 of a hin [2 liters] ��Hebrew 1/3 of a hin [1.3 liters] ��Hebrew 1/4 of a hin [1 liter]
