04Nm 29:1 "Celebrate the Festival of Trumpets each year on the first day of the appointed month in early autumn��. You must call an official day for holy assembly, and you may do no ordinary work. / ��Hebrew the first day of the seventh month. This day in the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred in September or October. This festival is celebrated today as Rosh Hashanah, the Jewish new year
