04Nm 29:7 "Ten days later, on the tenth day of the same month��, you must call another holy assembly. On that day, the Day of Atonement, the people must go without food and must do no ordinary work. / ��Hebrew On the tenth day of the seventh month; see 29.1 and the note there. This day in the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred in September or October. It is celebrated today as Yom Kippur
