04Nm 29:40 ��So Moses gave all of these instructions to the people of Israel as the LORD had commanded him. / ��Verse 29.40 is numbered 30.1 in Hebrew text
04Nm 30:1 ��Then Moses summoned the leaders of the tribes of Israel and told them, "This is what the LORD has commanded. / ��Verses 30.1-16 are numbered 30.2-17 in Hebrew text
04Nm 30:2 A man who makes a vow to the LORD or makes a pledge under oath must never break it. He must do exactly what he said he would do.
04Nm 30:3 "If a young woman makes a vow to the LORD or a pledge under oath while she is still living at her father's home,
04Nm 30:4 and her father hears of the vow or pledge and does not object to it, then all her vows and pledges will stand.
04Nm 30:5 But if her father refuses to let her fulfill the vow or pledge on the day he hears of it, then all her vows and pledges will become invalid. The LORD will forgive her because her father would not let her fulfill them.
04Nm 30:6 "Now suppose a young woman makes a vow or binds herself with an impulsive pledge and later marries.
04Nm 30:7 If her husband learns of her vow or pledge and does not object on the day he hears of it, her vows and pledges will stand.
04Nm 30:8 But if her husband refuses to accept her vow or impulsive pledge on the day he hears of it, he nullifies her commitments, and the LORD will forgive her.
04Nm 30:9 If, however, a woman is a widow or is divorced, she must fulfill all her vows and pledges.
04Nm 30:10 "But suppose a woman is married and living in her husband's home when she makes a vow or binds herself with a pledge.
04Nm 30:11 If her husband hears of it and does not object to it, her vow or pledge will stand.
04Nm 30:12 But if her husband refuses to accept it on the day he hears of it, her vow or pledge will be nullified, and the LORD will forgive her.
04Nm 30:13 So her husband may either confirm or nullify any vows or pledges she makes to deny herself.
04Nm 30:14 But if he does not object on the day he hears of it, then he is agreeing to all her vows and pledges.
04Nm 30:15 If he waits more than a day and then tries to nullify a vow or pledge, he will be punished for her guilt."
04Nm 30:16 These are the regulations the LORD gave Moses concerning relationships between a man and his wife, and between a father and a young daughter who still lives at home.
04Nm 31:1 Then the LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 31:2 "On behalf of the people of Israel, take revenge on the Midianites for leading them into idolatry. After that, you will die and join your ancestors."
04Nm 31:3 So Moses said to the people, "Choose some men, and arm them to fight the LORD's war of revenge against Midian.
04Nm 31:4 From each tribe of Israel, send 1,000 men into battle."
04Nm 31:5 So they chose 1,000 men from each tribe of Israel, a total of 12,000 men armed for battle.
04Nm 31:6 Then Moses sent them out, 1,000 men from each tribe, and Phinehas son of Eleazar the priest led them into battle. They carried along the holy objects of the sanctuary and the trumpets for sounding the charge.
04Nm 31:7 They attacked Midian as the LORD had commanded Moses, and they killed all the men.
04Nm 31:8 All five of the Midianite kings - Evi, Rekem, Zur, Hur, and Reba - died in the battle. They also killed Balaam son of Beor with the sword.
04Nm 31:9 Then the Israelite army captured the Midianite women and children and seized their cattle and flocks and all their wealth as plunder.
04Nm 31:10 They burned all the towns and villages where the Midianites had lived.
04Nm 31:11 After they had gathered the plunder and captives, both people and animals,
04Nm 31:12 they brought them all to Moses and Eleazar the priest, and to the whole community of Israel, which was camped on the plains of Moab beside the Jordan River, across from Jericho.
04Nm 31:13 Moses, Eleazar the priest, and all the leaders of the community went to meet them outside the camp.
04Nm 31:14 But Moses was furious with all the generals and captains�� who had returned from the battle. / ��Hebrew the commanders of thousands, and the commanders of hundreds; also in 31.48, 52, 54
04Nm 31:15 "Why have you let all the women live?" he demanded.
04Nm 31:16 "These are the very ones who followed Balaam's advice and caused the people of Israel to rebel against the LORD at Mount Peor. They are the ones who caused the plague to strike the LORD's people.
04Nm 31:17 So kill all the boys and all the women who have had intercourse with a man.
04Nm 31:18 Only the young girls who are virgins may live; you may keep them for yourselves.
04Nm 31:19 And all of you who have killed anyone or touched a dead body must stay outside the camp for seven days. You must purify yourselves and your captives on the third and seventh days.
04Nm 31:20 Purify all your clothing, too, and everything made of leather, goat hair, or wood."
04Nm 31:21 Then Eleazar the priest said to the men who were in the battle, "The LORD has given Moses this legal requirement.
04Nm 31:22 Anything made of gold, silver, bronze, iron, tin, or lead - 
04Nm 31:23 that is, all metals that do not burn - must be passed through fire in order to be made ceremonially pure. These metal objects must then be further purified with the water of purification. But everything that burns must be purified by the water alone.
04Nm 31:24 On the seventh day you must wash your clothes and be purified. Then you may return to the camp."
04Nm 31:25 And the LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 31:26 "You and Eleazar the priest and the family leaders of each tribe are to make a list of all the plunder taken in the battle, including the people and animals.
04Nm 31:27 Then divide the plunder into two parts, and give half to the men who fought the battle and half to the rest of the people.
04Nm 31:28 From the army's portion, first give the LORD his share of the plunder - one of every 500 of the prisoners and of the cattle, donkeys, sheep, and goats.
04Nm 31:29 Give this share of the army's half to Eleazar the priest as an offering to the LORD.
04Nm 31:30 From the half that belongs to the people of Israel, take one of every fifty of the prisoners and of the cattle, donkeys, sheep, goats, and other animals. Give this share to the Levites, who are in charge of maintaining the LORD's Tabernacle."
04Nm 31:31 So Moses and Eleazar the priest did as the LORD commanded Moses.
04Nm 31:32 The plunder remaining from everything the fighting men had taken totaled 675,000 sheep and goats,
04Nm 31:33 72,000 cattle,
04Nm 31:34 61,000 donkeys,
04Nm 31:35 and 32,000 virgin girls.
04Nm 31:36 Half of the plunder was given to the fighting men. It totaled 337,500 sheep and goats,
04Nm 31:37 of which 675 were the LORD's share;
04Nm 31:38 36,000 cattle, of which 72 were the LORD's share;
04Nm 31:39 30,500 donkeys, of which 61 were the LORD's share;
04Nm 31:40 and 16,000 virgin girls, of whom 32 were the LORD's share.
04Nm 31:41 Moses gave all the LORD's share to Eleazar the priest, just as the LORD had directed him.
04Nm 31:42 Half of the plunder belonged to the people of Israel, and Moses separated it from the half belonging to the fighting men.
04Nm 31:43 It totaled 337,500 sheep and goats,
04Nm 31:44 36,000 cattle,
04Nm 31:45 30,500 donkeys,
04Nm 31:46 and 16,000 virgin girls.
04Nm 31:47 From the half-share given to the people, Moses took one of every fifty prisoners and animals and gave them to the Levites, who maintained the LORD's Tabernacle. All this was done as the LORD had commanded Moses.
04Nm 31:48 Then all the generals and captains came to Moses
04Nm 31:49 and said, "We, your servants, have accounted for all the men who went out to battle under our command; not one of us is missing!
04Nm 31:50 So we are presenting the items of gold we captured as an offering to the LORD from our share of the plunder - armbands, bracelets, rings, earrings, and necklaces. This will purify our lives before the LORD and make us right with him��." / ��Or will make atonement for our lives before the LORD
04Nm 31:51 So Moses and Eleazar the priest received the gold from all the military commanders - all kinds of jewelry and crafted objects.
04Nm 31:52 In all, the gold that the generals and captains presented as a gift to the LORD weighed about 420 pounds��. / ��Hebrew 16,750 shekels [191 kilograms]
04Nm 31:53 All the fighting men had taken some of the plunder for themselves.
04Nm 31:54 So Moses and Eleazar the priest accepted the gifts from the generals and captains and brought the gold to the Tabernacle�� as a reminder to the LORD that the people of Israel belong to him. / ��Hebrew the Tent of Meeting
04Nm 32:1 The tribes of Reuben and Gad owned vast numbers of livestock. So when they saw that the lands of Jazer and Gilead were ideally suited for their flocks and herds,
04Nm 32:2 they came to Moses, Eleazar the priest, and the other leaders of the community. They said,
04Nm 32:3 "Notice the towns of Ataroth, Dibon, Jazer, Nimrah, Heshbon, Elealeh, Sibmah��, Nebo, and Beon. / ��As in Samaritan Pentateuch and Greek version (see also 32.38); Hebrew reads Sebam
04Nm 32:4 The LORD has conquered this whole area for the community of Israel, and it is ideally suited for all our livestock.
04Nm 32:5 If we have found favor with you, please let us have this land as our property instead of giving us land across the Jordan River."
04Nm 32:6 "Do you intend to stay here while your brothers go across and do all the fighting?" Moses asked the men of Gad and Reuben.
04Nm 32:7 "Why do you want to discourage the rest of the people of Israel from going across to the land the LORD has given them?
04Nm 32:8 Your ancestors did the same thing when I sent them from Kadesh-barnea to explore the land.
04Nm 32:9 After they went up to the valley of Eshcol and explored the land, they discouraged the people of Israel from entering the land the LORD was giving them.
04Nm 32:10 Then the LORD was very angry with them, and he vowed,
04Nm 32:11 'Of all those I rescued from Egypt, no one who is twenty years old or older will ever see the land I swore to give to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, for they have not obeyed me wholeheartedly.
04Nm 32:12 The only exceptions are Caleb son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite and Joshua son of Nun, for they have wholeheartedly followed the LORD.'
04Nm 32:13 "The LORD was angry with Israel and made them wander in the wilderness for forty years until the entire generation that sinned in the LORD's sight had died.
04Nm 32:14 But here you are, a brood of sinners, doing exactly the same thing! You are making the LORD even angrier with Israel.
04Nm 32:15 If you turn away from him like this and he abandons them again in the wilderness, you will be responsible for destroying this entire nation!"
04Nm 32:16 But they approached Moses and said, "We simply want to build pens for our livestock and fortified towns for our wives and children.
04Nm 32:17 Then we will arm ourselves and lead our fellow Israelites into battle until we have brought them safely to their land. Meanwhile, our families will stay in the fortified towns we build here, so they will be safe from any attacks by the local people.
04Nm 32:18 We will not return to our homes until all the people of Israel have received their portions of land.
04Nm 32:19 But we do not claim any of the land on the other side of the Jordan. We would rather live here on the east side and accept this as our grant of land."
04Nm 32:20 Then Moses said, "If you keep your word and arm yourselves for the LORD's battles,
04Nm 32:21 and if your troops cross the Jordan and keep fighting until the LORD has driven out his enemies,
04Nm 32:22 then you may return when the LORD has conquered the land. You will have fulfilled your duty to the LORD and to the rest of the people of Israel. And the land on the east side of the Jordan will be your property from the LORD.
04Nm 32:23 But if you fail to keep your word, then you will have sinned against the LORD, and you may be sure that your sin will find you out.
04Nm 32:24 Go ahead and build towns for your families and pens for your flocks, but do everything you have promised."
04Nm 32:25 Then the men of Gad and Reuben replied, "We, your servants, will follow your instructions exactly.
04Nm 32:26 Our children, wives, flocks, and cattle will stay here in the towns of Gilead.
04Nm 32:27 But all who are able to bear arms will cross over to fight for the LORD, just as you have said."
04Nm 32:28 So Moses gave orders to Eleazar the priest, Joshua son of Nun, and the leaders of the clans of Israel.
04Nm 32:29 He said, "The men of Gad and Reuben who are armed for battle must cross the Jordan with you to fight for the LORD. If they do, give them the land of Gilead as their property when the land is conquered.
04Nm 32:30 But if they refuse to arm themselves and cross over with you, then they must accept land with the rest of you in the land of Canaan."
04Nm 32:31 The tribes of Gad and Reuben said again, "We are your servants, and we will do as the LORD has commanded!
04Nm 32:32 We will cross the Jordan into Canaan fully armed to fight for the LORD, but our property will be here on this side of the Jordan."
04Nm 32:33 So Moses assigned land to the tribes of Gad, Reuben, and half the tribe of Manasseh son of Joseph. He gave them the territory of King Sihon of the Amorites and the land of King Og of Bashan - the whole land with its cities and surrounding lands.
04Nm 32:34 The descendants of Gad built the towns of Dibon, Ataroth, Aroer,
04Nm 32:35 Atroth-shophan, Jazer, Jogbehah,
04Nm 32:36 Beth-nimrah, and Beth-haran. These were all fortified towns with pens for their flocks.
04Nm 32:37 The descendants of Reuben built the towns of Heshbon, Elealeh, Kiriathaim,
04Nm 32:38 Nebo, Baal-meon, and Sibmah. They changed the names of some of the towns they conquered and rebuilt.
