04Nm 33:1 This is the route the Israelites followed as they marched out of Egypt under the leadership of Moses and Aaron.
04Nm 33:2 At the LORD's direction, Moses kept a written record of their progress. These are the stages of their march, identified by the different places where they stopped along the way.
04Nm 33:3 They set out from the city of Rameses in early spring - on the fifteenth day of the first month�� - on the morning after the first Passover celebration. The people of Israel left defiantly, in full view of all the Egyptians. / ��This day in the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred in late March, April, or early May
04Nm 33:4 Meanwhile, the Egyptians were burying all their firstborn sons, whom the LORD had killed the night before. The LORD had defeated the gods of Egypt that night with great acts of judgment!
04Nm 33:5 After leaving Rameses, the Israelites set up camp at Succoth.
04Nm 33:6 Then they left Succoth and camped at Etham on the edge of the wilderness.
04Nm 33:7 They left Etham and turned back toward Pi-hahiroth, opposite Baal-zephon, and camped near Migdol.
04Nm 33:8 They left Pi-hahiroth and crossed the Red Sea�� into the wilderness beyond. Then they traveled for three days into the Etham wilderness and camped at Marah. / ��Hebrew the sea
04Nm 33:9 They left Marah and camped at Elim, where there were twelve springs of water and seventy palm trees.
04Nm 33:10 They left Elim and camped beside the Red Sea��. / ��Hebrew sea of reeds; also in 33.11
04Nm 33:11 They left the Red Sea and camped in the wilderness of Sin��. / ��The geographical name Sin is related to Sinai and should not be confused with the English word sin
04Nm 33:12 They left the wilderness of Sin and camped at Dophkah.
04Nm 33:13 They left Dophkah and camped at Alush.
04Nm 33:14 They left Alush and camped at Rephidim, where there was no water for the people to drink.
04Nm 33:15 They left Rephidim and camped in the wilderness of Sinai.
04Nm 33:16 They left the wilderness of Sinai and camped at Kibroth-hattaavah.
04Nm 33:17 They left Kibroth-hattaavah and camped at Hazeroth.
04Nm 33:18 They left Hazeroth and camped at Rithmah.
04Nm 33:19 They left Rithmah and camped at Rimmon-perez.
04Nm 33:20 They left Rimmon-perez and camped at Libnah.
04Nm 33:21 They left Libnah and camped at Rissah.
04Nm 33:22 They left Rissah and camped at Kehelathah.
04Nm 33:23 They left Kehelathah and camped at Mount Shepher.
04Nm 33:24 They left Mount Shepher and camped at Haradah.
04Nm 33:25 They left Haradah and camped at Makheloth.
04Nm 33:26 They left Makheloth and camped at Tahath.
04Nm 33:27 They left Tahath and camped at Terah.
04Nm 33:28 They left Terah and camped at Mithcah.
04Nm 33:29 They left Mithcah and camped at Hashmonah.
04Nm 33:30 They left Hashmonah and camped at Moseroth.
04Nm 33:31 They left Moseroth and camped at Bene-jaakan.
04Nm 33:32 They left Bene-jaakan and camped at Hor-haggidgad.
04Nm 33:33 They left Hor-haggidgad and camped at Jotbathah.
04Nm 33:34 They left Jotbathah and camped at Abronah.
04Nm 33:35 They left Abronah and camped at Ezion-geber.
04Nm 33:36 They left Ezion-geber and camped at Kadesh in the wilderness of Zin.
04Nm 33:37 They left Kadesh and camped at Mount Hor, at the border of Edom.
04Nm 33:38 While they were at the foot of Mount Hor, Aaron the priest was directed by the LORD to go up the mountain, and there he died. This happened in midsummer, on the first day of the fifth month�� of the fortieth year after Israel's departure from Egypt. / ��This day in the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred in July or August
04Nm 33:39 Aaron was 123 years old when he died there on Mount Hor.
04Nm 33:40 At that time the Canaanite king of Arad, who lived in the Negev in the land of Canaan, heard that the people of Israel were approaching his land.
04Nm 33:41 Meanwhile, the Israelites left Mount Hor and camped at Zalmonah.
04Nm 33:42 Then they left Zalmonah and camped at Punon.
04Nm 33:43 They left Punon and camped at Oboth.
04Nm 33:44 They left Oboth and camped at Iye-abarim on the border of Moab.
04Nm 33:45 They left Iye-abarim�� and camped at Dibon-gad. / ��As in 33.44; Hebrew reads Iyim, another name for Iye-abarim
04Nm 33:46 They left Dibon-gad and camped at Almon-diblathaim.
04Nm 33:47 They left Almon-diblathaim and camped in the mountains east of the river��, near Mount Nebo. / ��Or the mountains of Abarim; also in 33.48
04Nm 33:48 They left the mountains east of the river and camped on the plains of Moab beside the Jordan River, across from Jericho.
04Nm 33:49 Along the Jordan River they camped from Beth-jeshimoth as far as the meadows of Acacia�� on the plains of Moab. / ��Hebrew as far as Abel-shittim
04Nm 33:50 While they were camped near the Jordan River on the plains of Moab opposite Jericho, the LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 33:51 "Give the following instructions to the people of Israel�� When you cross the Jordan River into the land of Canaan,
04Nm 33:52 you must drive out all the people living there. You must destroy all their carved and molten images and demolish all their pagan shrines.
04Nm 33:53 Take possession of the land and settle in it, because I have given it to you to occupy.
04Nm 33:54 You must distribute the land among the clans by sacred lot and in proportion to their size. A larger portion of land will be allotted to each of the larger clans, and a smaller portion will be allotted to each of the smaller clans. The decision of the sacred lot is final. In this way, the portions of land will be divided among your ancestral tribes.
04Nm 33:55 But if you fail to drive out the people who live in the land, those who remain will be like splinters in your eyes and thorns in your sides. They will harass you in the land where you live.
04Nm 33:56 And I will do to you what I had planned to do to them."
04Nm 34:1 Then the LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 34:2 "Give these instructions to the Israelites�� When you come into the land of Canaan, which I am giving you as your special possession, these will be the boundaries.
