04Nm 35:1 While Israel was camped beside the Jordan on the plains of Moab across from Jericho, the LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 35:2 "Command the people of Israel to give to the Levites from their property certain towns to live in, along with the surrounding pasturelands.
04Nm 35:3 These towns will be for the Levites to live in, and the surrounding lands will provide pasture for their cattle, flocks, and other livestock.
04Nm 35:4 The pastureland assigned to the Levites around these towns will extend 1,500 feet�� from the town walls in every direction. / ��Hebrew 1,000 cubits [460 meters]
04Nm 35:5 Measure off 3,000 feet�� outside the town walls in every direction - east, south, west, north - with the town at the center. This area will serve as the larger pastureland for the towns. / ��Hebrew 2,000 cubits [920 meters]
04Nm 35:6 "Six of the towns you give the Levites will be cities of refuge, where a person who has accidentally killed someone can flee for safety. In addition, give them forty-two other towns.
04Nm 35:7 In all, forty-eight towns with the surrounding pastureland will be given to the Levites.
04Nm 35:8 These towns will come from the property of the people of Israel. The larger tribes will give more towns to the Levites, while the smaller tribes will give fewer. Each tribe will give property in proportion to the size of its land."
04Nm 35:9 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 35:10 "Give the following instructions to the people of Israel."When you cross the Jordan into the land of Canaan,
04Nm 35:11 designate cities of refuge to which people can flee if they have killed someone accidentally.
04Nm 35:12 These cities will be places of protection from a dead person's relatives who want to avenge the death. The slayer must not be put to death before being tried by the community.
04Nm 35:13 Designate six cities of refuge for yourselves,
04Nm 35:14 three on the east side of the Jordan River and three on the west in the land of Canaan.
04Nm 35:15 These cities are for the protection of Israelites, foreigners living among you, and traveling merchants. Anyone who accidentally kills someone may flee there for safety.
04Nm 35:16 "But if someone strikes and kills another person with a piece of iron, it is murder, and the murderer must be executed.
04Nm 35:17 Or if someone with a stone in his hand strikes and kills another person, it is murder, and the murderer must be put to death.
04Nm 35:18 Or if someone strikes and kills another person with a wooden object, it is murder, and the murderer must be put to death.
04Nm 35:19 The victim's nearest relative is responsible for putting the murderer to death. When they meet, the avenger must put the murderer to death.
04Nm 35:20 So if someone hates another person and pushes him or throws a dangerous object at him and he dies, it is murder.
04Nm 35:21 Or if someone hates another person and hits him with a fist and he dies, it is murder. In such cases, the avenger must put the murderer to death when they meet.
04Nm 35:22 "But suppose someone pushes another person without having shown previous hostility, or throws something that unintentionally hits another person,
04Nm 35:23 or accidentally drops a huge stone on someone, though they were not enemies, and the person dies.
04Nm 35:24 If this should happen, the community must follow these regulations in making a judgment between the slayer and the avenger, the victim's nearest relative.
04Nm 35:25 The community must protect the slayer from the avenger and must escort the slayer back to live in the city of refuge to which he fled. There he must remain until the death of the high priest, who was anointed with the sacred oil.
04Nm 35:26 "But if the slayer ever leaves the limits of the city of refuge,
04Nm 35:27 and the avenger finds him outside the city and kills him, it will not be considered murder.
04Nm 35:28 The slayer should have stayed inside the city of refuge until the death of the high priest. But after the death of the high priest, the slayer may return to his own property.
04Nm 35:29 These are legal requirements for you to observe from generation to generation, wherever you may live.
04Nm 35:30 "All murderers must be put to death, but only if evidence is presented by more than one witness. No one may be put to death on the testimony of only one witness.
04Nm 35:31 Also, you must never accept a ransom payment for the life of someone judged guilty of murder and subject to execution; murderers must always be put to death.
04Nm 35:32 And never accept a ransom payment from someone who has fled to a city of refuge, allowing a slayer to return to his property before the death of the high priest.
04Nm 35:33 This will ensure that the land where you live will not be polluted, for murder pollutes the land. And no sacrifice except the execution of the murderer can purify the land from murder��. / ��Or can make atonement for murder
04Nm 35:34 You must not defile the land where you live, for I live there myself. I am the LORD, who lives among the people of Israel."
04Nm 36:1 Then the heads of the clans of Gilead - descendants of Makir, son of Manasseh, son of Joseph - came to Moses and the family leaders of Israel with a petition.
04Nm 36:2 They said, "Sir, the LORD instructed you to divide the land by sacred lot among the people of Israel. You were told by the LORD to give the grant of land owned by our brother Zelophehad to his daughters.
04Nm 36:3 But if they marry men from another tribe, their grants of land will go with them to the tribe into which they marry. In this way, the total area of our tribal land will be reduced.
04Nm 36:4 Then when the Year of Jubilee comes, their portion of land will be added to that of the new tribe, causing it to be lost forever to our ancestral tribe."
04Nm 36:5 So Moses gave the Israelites this command from the LORD�� "The claim of the men of the tribe of Joseph is legitimate.
04Nm 36:6 This is what the LORD commands concerning the daughters of Zelophehad�� Let them marry anyone they like, as long as it is within their own ancestral tribe.
04Nm 36:7 None of the territorial land may pass from tribe to tribe, for all the land given to each tribe must remain within the tribe to which it was first allotted.
04Nm 36:8 The daughters throughout the tribes of Israel who are in line to inherit property must marry within their tribe, so that all the Israelites will keep their ancestral property.
04Nm 36:9 No grant of land may pass from one tribe to another; each tribe of Israel must keep its allotted portion of land."
04Nm 36:10 The daughters of Zelophehad did as the LORD commanded Moses.
04Nm 36:11 Mahlah, Tirzah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Noah all married cousins on their father's side.
04Nm 36:12 They married into the clans of Manasseh son of Joseph. Thus, their inheritance of land remained within their ancestral tribe.
04Nm 36:13 These are the commands and regulations that the LORD gave to the people of Israel through Moses while they were camped on the plains of Moab beside the Jordan River across from Jericho.
